    <h2>4. Filter Coffee Machines (Drip / Batch Brew)</h2>
    <p>Filter coffee machines brew large batches of coffee by slowly passing hot water through a filter basket containing ground coffee. The result is a milder, less concentrated coffee than espresso, typically served in larger cups. Filter coffee machines are the dominant technology in hotels, corporate offices, American-style cafés, and anywhere that needs to serve large numbers of people quickly.</p>
    <p>In India, the term "filter coffee" also specifically refers to South Indian-style filter coffee — a strong decoction brewed through a traditional metal filter and mixed with hot milk and sugar. We cover both types below.</p>

