    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the price of a commercial espresso machine in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Commercial espresso machine prices in India in 2026 range from ₹30,000 for a basic single-group entry-level machine to ₹13 lakh or more for a top-tier La Marzocco 3-group machine. Most serious cafés in India invest ₹2.5 lakh to ₹5 lakh in a 2-group machine from brands like Nuova Simonelli or Rancilio. Remember to budget for a commercial grinder (₹55K–₹1.5L) in addition to the espresso machine.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which is the best commercial coffee machine for a café in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For most Indian cafés, the Nuova Simonelli Appia Life 2-group is the best all-round choice — excellent build quality, outstanding espresso performance, and one of the best service networks in India for a premium Italian brand. For operators who want lower skill requirements and more consistency across staff, the Jura GIGA 10 (super-automatic) or WMF 1500 S+ are excellent alternatives. For small cafés on tighter budgets, a DeLonghi commercial machine offers Italian quality with the best service network in the country.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the difference between a semi-automatic and super-automatic coffee machine? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A semi-automatic espresso machine requires a trained barista to grind, dose, tamp, and control extraction manually — the machine provides consistent pressure and temperature. A super-automatic machine (bean-to-cup) automates all of these steps at the touch of a button. Semi-automatics produce better espresso in the hands of a skilled barista; super-automatics produce more consistent results regardless of who operates them. For cafés where coffee quality and barista craft are brand differentiators, choose semi-automatic. For hotels, offices, and high-volume outlets where consistency and ease of operation matter more, choose super-automatic.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is La Marzocco available in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, La Marzocco is available in India through Kaapi Machines (Bengaluru), which is the authorised distributor. La Marzocco machines are available in Delhi, Mumbai, Bengaluru, and through Kaapi Machines' pan-India shipping. Prices range from approximately ₹2.2 lakh for the Linea Mini to ₹13+ lakh for a 3-group Strada. Service support is available in the major metros but is more limited than brands like DeLonghi or Jura.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How many cups can a commercial espresso machine make per hour? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A single-group commercial espresso machine can produce approximately 60–80 espresso shots per hour in continuous use. A 2-group machine can produce 120–160 shots per hour. A 3-group machine can produce 180–250+ shots per hour. In practice, actual output depends on the barista's workflow, drink complexity (lattes and cappuccinos take longer than straight espressos), and whether the machine has time to recover steam pressure between milky drinks. A 2-group machine with a skilled barista can comfortably service 150–200 cups per day in a normal café trading pattern.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What maintenance does a commercial coffee machine need? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Commercial espresso machines require: daily backflushing with cleaning tablets, weekly deep cleaning of group heads and steam wands, monthly inspection of seals and gaskets, and an annual professional service. Water filters should be changed every 3–6 months depending on local water hardness. Budget 5–8% of the machine's purchase price per year for maintenance. Installing a water softener is the single most cost-effective maintenance investment you can make — hard water causes scale buildup that is the leading cause of commercial espresso machine failure in India.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What coffee machine is best for a cloud kitchen or dark kitchen? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For a cloud kitchen or dark kitchen adding coffee to the menu, a super-automatic bean-to-cup machine is generally the best choice. Delivery coffee needs to be consistent, fast, and not dependent on a dedicated barista. A Jura commercial machine (₹1.5L–₹4.5L) or DeLonghi professional super-automatic (₹1L–₹1.8L) will produce good quality coffee with minimal training and maintenance. If specialty espresso drinks are a significant part of your menu, consider a 1-group semi-automatic with a grinder — but factor in the barista training cost.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

